Blockson — Provenance Notice
============================

Blockson was built largely by AI coding agents (large language models)
operating under human direction, review, and testing. A human maintainer set
the architecture, the requirements, and the acceptance bar; the bulk of the
implementation, documentation, and tests were produced by AI agents and then
reviewed.

This is disclosed in the spirit of transparency. It does not change how the
project should be judged: correctness and safety are enforced by the machine
validators (engine/validate-*.js) and the end-to-end proof suite
(engine/_run-proofs.js, run with `npm test`), and the same bar applies to every
contribution regardless of how it was authored — by hand or with an LLM. See
CONTRIBUTING.md.

The project is shared as-is under the MIT License (see LICENSE), on a
best-effort basis and with no guarantee of support.
